ulent magnetic fields. The depolarization, corresponding to a standard\ndeviation of the Rotation Measures as high as $\\sigma_{\\rm RM}= 212\\pm23\\rm\n\\,rad\\,m^{-2}$, suggests that the brush is located in or behind the ICM. Our\nfindings indicate that the Toothbrush can be consistently explained by the\nstandard scenario for relic formation\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Aug 2020 14:53:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 19 Sep 2020 17:54:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-14"}
